
Video 62(b) 
-- First we need to install nodejs on ec2 to run nodejs project

- NVM -- Node version manager manage the version system in nodejs
    we are going to install nodejs whenever install nodejs will get npm
- here npm is node program manager it will install required dependencies from package.json

- lock.package.json -- this is to lock the version for dependencies to the project

- npm install -- will download all dependencies

- npm start


-->


- in docker ec2-
    - apt-get install git
    - git --version
    - git clone https://github.com/CloudTechDevOps/swiggy-nodejs-devops-project.git
    - cd <project_folder>
    - Inside the project folder
        - vi Dockerfile
            * FROM node:16
            * WORKDIR /app
            * COPY package*json ./
            * RUN npm install
            * COPY . .
            * RUN npm un build
            * EXPOSE 3000
            * ENTRYPOINT 
        - incase multiple docker files available then we need to use
            * docker build -f <Dockerfilename> -t <image_name> .
            * docker build -f Dockefile1 -t test .
        - docker build -t nodejs .
--> 
        












